<section class="veto-logic-section">
  <h2>The Architecture of Certainty</h2>
  <div class="logic-card">
    <h3>Why Deterministic?</h3>
    <p>
      Traditional LLM guardrails are <strong>probabilistic</strong>—they "guess" if a transaction is safe based on intent. 
      <strong>VetoLayer</strong> is <strong>deterministic</strong>. 
    </p>
    <p>
      We implement hard-logic intercepts at the network layer to freeze unauthorized tool calls in <strong><150µs</strong>. 
      If the cryptographic handshake isn't present, the transaction cannot execute.
    </p>
    <p class="tagline"><em>"No Veto, No Flow."</em></p>
  </div>
</section>
